DATABASE:
1. Users Table
Purpose: Stores information about the users (both students and admins).
Columns:
id (Primary Key, Auto Increment)
name (String)
email (String, Unique)
password (String)
is_admin (Boolean, default to false for students and true for admins)
created_at (Timestamp)
updated_at (Timestamp)


2. Books Table
Purpose: Stores information about the books available in the library.
Columns:
id (Primary Key, Auto Increment)
title (String)
author (String)
description (Text)
created_at (Timestamp)
updated_at (Timestamp)


3. Borrows Table
Purpose: Tracks which books have been borrowed by which users and their return status.
Columns:
id (Primary Key, Auto Increment)
user_id (Foreign Key referencing users.id)
book_id (Foreign Key referencing books.id)
borrowed_at (Timestamp)
return_due_date (Timestamp)
returned_at (Timestamp, Nullable)
created_at (Timestamp)
updated_at (Timestamp)